Primary site is:
	http://www.ams-ix.net/

About Arpswiffer
----------------

Arpswiffer is a tool that sweeps up stray ARP queries from a LAN. It
listens on an ethernet interface and if the ARP rate for a particular
IP address goes over the threshold, it starts faking responses.

This is especially useful on large peering LANs where a router hang can
result in large ARP (broadcast) storms.

Requirements
------------

	* GNU make
	* Perl (>= 5.8)
	* Perl modules:
		- Net::PcapUtils
		- NetPacket::Ethernet
		- NetPacket::ARP
		- NetPacket::IP
		- Time::HiRes
		- Net::ARP
		- Sys::Syslog
		- Net::IPv4Addr

Installation
------------

DEBIAN:

1. Copy config.mk.dist to config.mk
2. Optionally edit config.mk (see below)
3. Run "make dpkg"
4. "dpkg --install *.deb"

OTHER SYSTEMS:

1. Copy config.mk.dist to config.mk

2. Look at the start of "config.mk" and set correct values for:

 (MUST be set correctly)

	PERL         (/usr/bin/perl)
	IFCONFIG     (/sbin/ifconfig)
	SPONGE_VAR   (/var/run/arpswiffer)

 (MAY be changed)

	DIRPREFIX
	BINPREFIX
	DOCPREFIX
	BINDIR
	LIBROOT
	INSTLIB
	MANDIR
	DOCDIR

	SECTION
	FILESECTION

3. run "make"

4. run "make install"


Documentation
-------------

See the "arpswiffer" man page, or "perldoc arpswiffer".
